<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-20T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-20T09:00:00-05:00" n="754" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/499: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia (<persName type="from">Skinner</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-20T16:00:00+02:00">April 20, 1932—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 20—2:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>39. Violent anti-Japanese campaign in <hi rend="italic">Izvestia</hi>
                            April 15th and 18th, <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> 16th, <hi rend="italic">Trud</hi> 17th, claiming that Japanese military
                            circles are more and more in power, they want war, are inflaming public
                            opinion, are responsible for anti-Soviet activities of White Guards, are
                            using Manchuria as base of operations against Russia.</p>
                        <p>Tass communiqué in <hi rend="italic">Izvestia</hi> April 18th that
                            Soviets have requested change of Chinese Consul in Blagoveshchensk on
                            account of abuse of code in sending messages purporting to be from
                            General <persName corresp="#p_MC1">Ma</persName>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>